Author: VoskCoin#1869
Content:
I was talking to Luxor today about their current pools and asked about pirate, he said he was contemplating it and said if he added pirate he wanted to add KMD too because he likes KMD and asked if I could get him in touch with ARRR/KMD devs so I started a group chat with @FishyGuts and the 3 Luxor tech team members

Now Nick@ luxor is planning to or already has reached out to @ComputerGenie 👴🏼📢 because he was the one who created pirate solo, I didn't do this for this "campaign" and I don't care if we lose

However I wanted to share a very real result of basically my goals and potential value of expanding the KMD ecosystem whether its with a lot of small victories or also larger ones down the road. I believe everyone would agree a professional mining pool (which also sports a new payout scheme to the coins PPS) is always a welcome addition, especially for multiple KMD coins -- whats next maybe they'll add a veruscoin pool for @miketout 

The value proposition of my NN campaign could be explained in the example above, so contrary to @Alright criticism I believe I have one of the most unique proposals that aims to add value in a way that is not heavily focused on currently or historically.

Author: PHBA2061#2530
Content:
I was thinking about that and this is my conclusion, please correct me if I'm wrong :
On mainnet there are 64 NN & minsigs is 13, which means only 13 NN are required to sign a nota transaction. So worst case scenario,  if 64 NN are separated into 4 groups  (each group has 13 NN at least and they don't see each other), theoretically we could see quadruple notas. It is not a risk as long as all NN are on the same chain, the only thing is they spend 4 times as much as required.
Please correct me if I'm wrong
